This restaurant is pretty good! The food tastes very well and they deliver fast! However, I had to remove 2 stars from what would otherwise be a 5 star review because of a sneaky business practice they use. You have been warned. They charge a $5 delivery fee and you have the option of paying a tip as well. I always tip 20%. However, I found out (from my payment methods) that they give the $5 tip to the delivery driver. So the delivery driver gets $5 + tip. Usually, the delivery fee is used to cover costs of car gas, but I strongly suspect that they do not use the $5 for that. I would recommend not getting delivery and instead going in person and ordering.

WOW I'm speechless at the service I just experienced . I ordered food for delivery and paid via telephone for it. After an hour of still not receiving the food, I called back to inquire on its whereabouts. I was told it was on way... 30 min later, and still no delivery. I called back multiple times, each time they angrily told me it's coming and then hung up on me before i could say anything else. Finally, after multiple phone calls, the man told me he doesnt know, and that I should call his delivery guy, gave me the number for him and hung up on me again. I called the delivery guy, he said he was 15 min away. Over 15 min passed...At this point the food was ordered hours prior. I called back the restaurant,  was hung up on several more times. Finally they didnt hang up, and told me the driver couldnt find our location. I called back again to be told that the driver had 'dropped the food off, but no-one was home"....  At this point, will have to call me cc company to dispute the charges.  I'm completely appalled at the atrocious service I experienced here tonight.
